A human rights lawyer, Barrister Ifeanyi Ejiofor has called on Anambra State Governor, Charles Soludo to caution officers of the state task force to desist from further harassment of innocent civilians in the guise of enforcing the law.  Ejiofor, who is the lead counsel for Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), said the gross abuse of public office by the power-drunk officers is a grave disregard for the sanctity of human life which he described as ridiculous and unacceptable. Ifeanyi Ejiofor Ejiofor disclosed this in a statement on Friday in Abuja while reacting to the assault and humiliation of Prophet Chukwuemeka Ohanaemere aka Odumeje in a viral video by security operatives.  Officials of the task force on Thursday physically assaulted the controversial cleric.  The founder of the Mountain of Holy Ghost Intervention and Deliverance Ministry was said to have received a beating while trying to stop the state task force from demolishing his church in Onitsha. See Also






