1 Day Ago The lawyer said the action of the officers was wrong, barbaric, uncivilised and in gross violation of the extant rights of the cleric. He also demanded reparation for the infraction to assuage the trauma the clergyman must have gone through, which he said must be followed by an unreserved apology.  The statement read in part, "Yesterday, being the 7th day of July 2022, video clips of the grievous assault on Prophet Chukwuemeka Odumeje surfaced online. We were not quick to jump to conclusions until necessary contacts were made to ascertain their authenticity.  "I personally called Prophet Odumeje to confirm the authenticity or otherwise of the degrading video clips.  "Governor Soludo should be properly guided to immediately (keep a tight) rein on the lawless enforcement officers he deployed to torment an innocent civilian, in the guise of task force.  "It is sad to note that this is not a palatable start for the hitherto, highly rated Governor of Anambra state, who is just spending his first 100 days in office, still issuing statements without tangible results yet.  "We, the Anambrarians are not averse to his Excellency's people-orientated policy, geared towards bringing the proceeds of good governance home "  The statement urged the governor to maintain civility by sanctioning the activities of these lawless officers around him. It also condemned the reckless killings and genocidal massacre of innocent civilians by overzealous law enforcement agents deployed to Anambra to maintain law and order.  He added that the gory pictures and video clips of youths in Ogbaru hacked to death in their prime were heart-wrenching.  The statement, therefore, called for adequate profiling and strict adherence to professional rules of engagement to avoid the killing of innocent citizens as we witnessed in Ogbaru weeks ago.  "For the records, I am among the few, who publicly condemned the heinous criminal activities of the men of underworld going on in our land, as well as the senseless killings by the enemies of our people which criminality also led to the unfortunate kidnapping of my Aunty. I never hesitated in urging our youth and fellow Anambrarians to join hands in reclaiming our lands from these monsters.  “I still stand by this position and shall continue to encourage all and sundry to resist these criminalities.  "However, in so doing by the relevant law enforcement agents and volunteers, caution must not be thrown to the wind.  "There must be adequate profiling and strict adherence to professional rules of engagement to avoid killing of innocent citizens in the process, just as the unfortunate situation we witnessed in Ogbaru weeks ago.  "I, therefore, urge Governor Soludo, to set proper machinery in motion to ensure that the activities of these trigger-happy Law Enforcement Agents are strictly monitored and regularly appraised. Ejiofor added. 